fields.headline:
Hey, I’m Josh —
a curious mind writing code,
wrangling data,
and building smart things with heart.
fields.about:
Hi, I’m Josh — a curious mind from Abuja with a heart for solving problems and a growing passion for AI, data science, and all things tech. I’m currently pursuing a degree in Computer Science at the University of Abuja, and I love using code to build things that make life easier, smarter, and sometimes just more fun.
 I’ve been exploring Python, Django, data analysis, and machine learning — constantly learning and growing, one project at a time.

fields.expertise: Python & Django,  Machine Learning, Version Control, Responsive Web Design, APIs , Data Analysis & Visualization, Problem Solving

fields.title: Data Entry Volunteer
fields.description: Supported organizational workflows by entering and formatting large volumes of data into spreadsheets. Maintained high accuracy levels while digitizing reports and contributing to productive and timely reports.

fields.title: Media Officer
fields.description: Managed real-time visual content for weekly services using EasyWorship and VideoPsalm. Oversaw projector displays, coordinated with audio teams, and ensured seamless transitions during live worship streaming and teaching events.

fields.title: Data Science Intern
fields.description: Worked on data-driven projects including customer satisfaction prediction and personalized health recommendation systems. Gained practical experience with machine learning models, feature engineering, data visualization, and statistical analysis.

Attended the School for the Gifted, Gwagwalada, where I built a strong academic foundation, developed a passion for problem-solving, and cultivated leadership, teamwork, and critical thinking skills in a competitive and intellectually driven environment.

Pursuing a Bachelor's degree in Computer Science at the University of Abuja, with a strong focus on software development, data structures, algorithms, and real-world problem solving through technology.

fields.title: Deployed Healthcare Recommendation service
fields.description: The project successfully developed a django-deployed robust diabetes prediction system, achieving high accuracy and providing meaningful recommendations.

fields.title: E-Learning Integrated system (Backend)
fields.description: This project began as a school student project, which I scaled into a comprehensive demo LMS capable of being expanded to serve real institutional needs. This platform supports multi-role user authentication (students, lecturers, and visitors), course management, dashboard personalization, e.t.c..

fields.title: Data and Exploratory Analysis
fields.description: In my DataCamp's Python Data associate Spectrum Shades LLC Project, I conducted data cleaning, exploratory analysis, and statistical analysis to get data-driven insights and strategic analysis across four structured tasks.

fields.title: Predicting Customer satisfaction
fields.description: This project focuses on predicting customer satisfaction levels while also highlighting data visualizations for an airline service based on various key factors. This provides valuable insights with comparisons, relationships and plots into vital areas where improvements can enhance passenger experience.

fields.title: Healthcare recommender Model and Algorithm
fields.description: This project uses machine learning to analyze patient data and predict diabetes levels by processing key health indicators. It also suggests lifestyle or medical adjustments, aiming to improve diabetes care with generated actionable recommendations.

fields.title: GitHub Repo QuickSearch CLI Tool
fields.description:
A simple yet functional Python command-line script that automates GitHub repository search. It scrapes the top repositories' results based on a user's search keywords and opens them in the browser instantly.
This was one of my earliest scripting projects, where I explored: HTTP requests, BeautifulSoup, webbrowser etc..
